.TH "snd_hda_mixer_amp_tlv" 9 "snd_hda_mixer_amp_tlv" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hda_mixer_amp_tlv \- TLV callback for a standard AMP mixer volume
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_hda_mixer_amp_tlv
.BI "(struct snd_kcontrol *kcontrol "  ","
.BI "int op_flag "  ","
.BI "unsigned int size "  ","
.BI "unsigned int __user *_tlv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kcontrol" 12
ctl element
.IP "op_flag" 12
operation flag
.IP "size" 12
byte size of input TLV
.IP "_tlv" 12
TLV data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The control element is supposed to have the private_value field
set up via HDA_COMPOSE_AMP_VAL*() or related macros.
